node.text: Follow along as Jamie show us how to make a delicious, nutritious spin on classic chips and dip. Here's the recipe! http://www.cookinglight.com/eating-smart/recipe-makeovers/lower-calorie-french-onion-dip

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on July 21, 2021. May be an image of pizza.

node.text: If you're pro-pepper, this combination of sweet and heat will tickle your tastebuds—and it takes less than half an hour to make! Click the link in our bio for the recipe: Pepper-Only Pizza 🌶️🍕

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on July 21, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: This summery riff on saltimbocca is simplicity itself, with big flavor hits provided by prosciutto and heirloom tomatoes. Fragrant shallots, grated to a pulp, serve as a marinade for the chicken, yielding delicious results. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 🍅🍗

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on July 20, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: This quick taco filling is perfect for #tacotuesday. Poblano chiles bring rich, earthy flavor but little to no heat. If you want to add a little spice, add some crushed red pepper when you sauté the mushrooms. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 🌮🌮🌮

node.text: In this fun twist on shrimp and grits, the shrimp mixture takes on bold flavors from Creole seasoning, smoked paprika, thyme, and garlic—making for a robust mixture that’s complemented by the sweetness of the creamed corn. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 🌽🍤

node.text: These crab cakes hold together best with dry, finely ground whole-wheat breadcrumbs. Chives have a delicate onion flavor that won't overpower the crab. Click the link in our bio for the recipe which can easily be doubled to serve 4.

node.text: How about our Mustard Green Pesto and Egg Open-Faced Sandwich for breakfast? Any extra pesto will keep refrigerated for 4 days and frozen for up to a month. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 🍳🍞

node.text: Our finishing touches--a hit of herbs, peppery olive oil, and tangy vinegar--make these shrimp the freshest, most irresistible appetizer. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 🍤🍤🍤

node.text: Beets bring earthy flavor and bright, bold color to cured salmon served on sourdough toasts with fromage blanc, hard-cooked egg, radish slices, and a few drops of tangerine-infused oil. Click the link in our bio for the recipe: Beet-Cured Salmon

node.text: Looking for an afternoon pick-me-up? Try this craveable combo of invigorating jalapeño, refreshing pineapple, and sweet beets, which naturally increase blood flow to the brain. Click the link in our bio for the full recipe! 🍍

node.text: Our Asian-inspired nachos are wildly flavorful with a tangy kick from kimchi, which is often fermented and aged, delivering gut-healthy probiotics. Try adding diced avocado, chopped bell peppers, or jalapenos for extra heat. Click the link in our bio for the full recipe! 🔥🌶️

node.text: Move over, potatoes. Cauliflower is stealing the side dish spotlight. It's low-carb, high-fiber profile makes cauliflower a winner for many people watching their calorie counts. Click the link in our bio for our delicious roasted cauliflower recipe!
